# Blu Collar Web Solutions - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
Web design agency site targeting blue-collar contractors.
Exported from Webflow, rebuilt as a clean static site.
Audience: plumbers, roofers, HVAC techs, electricians, landscapers.

## Tech Stack
- Plain HTML, CSS, JavaScript (no framework unless explicitly added)
- No build tools required unless introduced intentionally
- Deployed on Vercel or Netlify

## Code Style
- Use semantic HTML5 elements (`section`, `nav`, `main`, `article`, `footer`)
- CSS: use custom properties (variables) for all colors, fonts, and spacing
- Mobile-first responsive design; always check mobile layout
- No inline styles
- Class names must use kebab-case (e.g., `.hero-section`, `.pricing-card`)
- Keep CSS organized in this order: layout -> components -> utilities
- JavaScript must stay vanilla; no jQuery or unnecessary libraries

## Content and Copy Rules
- Write all copy at a 6th-8th grade reading level with plain, direct language
- Avoid jargon: use clear outcomes like "get more calls"
- Write for busy tradespeople, not marketers
- Every section must communicate a clear visitor outcome

## Design Principles
- Brand colors: primary blue (`#1B3A6B` or nearest export match), white, light gray
- Typography: match Webflow export fonts
- Maintain consistent spacing using existing CSS variables
- CTAs should be action-oriented ("Get Started", "See Our Work", "Book a Call")

## What Not To Do
- Do not add Lorem Ipsum or placeholder content; flag it instead
- Do not add dependencies or npm packages without approval
- Do not change visual design without explicit instruction
- Do not remove existing sections without confirmation
- Do not auto-format the entire codebase without asking first

## Git Practices
- Use Conventional Commits format (e.g., `feat: ...`, `fix: ...`, `chore: ...`)
- Keep one logical change per commit
- Always confirm before committing or pushing

## Known Issues To Fix (Do Not Auto-Fix)
- Lorem ipsum testimonials need replacing
- Broken feature comparison table on pricing page
- Leftover Webflow template content (VR/Matterport section, IPO blog posts)
- Pricing tiers need "Everything in [tier], plus..." language
- Missing About/founder section
- No phone number or location in header/footer
- Missing FAQ section on pricing page
